# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# Each entry must be reviewed and re-evaluated when the base image is updated.
#
# These CVEs affect Ruby default gems bundled inside ruby:4.0.4-alpine that
# cannot be removed without breaking the Ruby runtime. The application itself
# uses patched versions (json >= 2.19.5, net-imap >= 0.6.4) via Gemfile.
# Re-evaluate when ruby:4.0.5-alpine or later is released.

# CVE-2026-33210: json 2.18.0 (Ruby 4.0.4 default gem) - DoS/info disclosure
# Fixed in: >= 2.19.2 | App uses: 2.19.5 via Gemfile | Base image not yet patched
CVE-2026-33210

# CVE-2026-42246: net-imap 0.6.2 (Ruby 4.0.4 default gem) - STARTTLS stripping
# Fixed in: >= 0.6.4 | App uses: 0.6.4 via Gemfile | Base image not yet patched
CVE-2026-42246
